election_record.label: Massachusetts 1792 Electoral College, Eastern District

overview.note: A majority of votes was required to be elected. As no electors received a majority of votes, the Massachusetts General Court selected the three electors. Nathaniel Wells, Daniel Coney and Peleg Wadsworth were selected.

There were no affiliations or elector declarations in the Original Election Returns. Nathaniel Wells, Daniel Coney and Peleg Wadsworth voted for George Washington and John Adams in the Electoral College.
